  "text": "These three properties are enough to show upper limits for F , on the model of the Beardwood, Halton, Hammersley theorem. To have the full limits, the umbrella theorem of [CITATION_1] also requires to check a few more properties of a so-called boundary functional associated with F . Next, let us present a classical optimization problem which does not enter the above picture. Given two multi-subsets of R d with the same cardinality, X = {X 1 , . . . , X n } and Y = {Y 1 , . . . , Y n }, the cost of the minimal bipartite matching of X and Y is defined as",
